    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-29T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="837"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d837">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–2954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-29T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 29, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 541. Repeated information Paris 517,
                    London 332, Saigon 224, Moscow 149. <persName corresp="#p_RJ1">Roux</persName>
                    reports that at <persName corresp="#p_KVV1">Kuznetsov</persName> dinner for
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> last night, Russians appeared
                    anxious be “helpful” on control problems, <pb facs="1286" n="1260"
                        xml:id="pg_1260"/> but no concrete suggestions or discussion developed. He
                    said Russians appear genuinely puzzled by attitude US and <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> here, stating they not know what US wanted.
                        (<persName corresp="#p_RJ1">Roux</persName> said this was good thing.)</p>
                <p>French gained impression while Soviet insistent on inclusion Poland or
                    Czechoslovakia and India under 3-nation composition, would be willing substitute
                    for Indonesia non-Asian country more “neutral” on France’s side.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
